text: Didar Khamza (born 15 February 1997) is a Kazakhstani judoka. He won a silver medal at the 2016 Asian Judo Championships and competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics, where he was eliminated in the second round.Didar Khamza . nbcolympics.com ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Kazakhstani male judoka Category:Olympic judoka of Kazakhstan Category:Judoka at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Judoka at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Asian Games gold medalists for Kazakhstan Category:Asian Games silver medalists for Kazakhstan Category:Asian Games medalists in judo Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games
